My final compile of this map for The ["Time Traveler"](http://www.gamebanana.com/news/20032 "The "Time Traveler" Mapping Contest") Mapping Contest. I don't have much free time left, so I thought I'd wrap up this project and hope for the best. I took a lot of previous comments to heart, and looked up some Tutorials here to help me on some things I was lost about. I hope you enjoy this map in-game as much as I enjoyed making it! I find it fun for even bot killing. :)

### **Features & Background**

- Full recreation of the original fy_poolday for source.
- Set 50 years ahead of the original map theme. Thick foliage has overgrown the place, and a shift in climates has resulted in thunderstorms.
- This map has built in thunder and lightning sequences, as well as precipitation outside to fully incorporate an eery and somewhat challenging environment that I was looking for.
- A shift in times has resulted in the Terrorists wanting to bomb the old facility to further provoke fear and lack of trust among the citizens of the local town.
- There are also buyzones in this map, a new twist in this version that the original did not have.
- Full support for 64-man servers, although this map is recommended for around 32-36 players for best experience.
- Tweaked navigational mesh with included area naming for a full experience.
- Addition of radar map.

### **Known Bugs**

- Some very minor lighting issues, primiarly around the upper ivy/grass bordering. Some prop lighting issues too.
- Slightly bugged bumpmaping of the red and blue floor tiling.
- Slight navigation issues around Bombsite B (diving board).

### **Changelog**

#### Alpha 1 -> Alpha 4

- Removal of dense smoke as it proved quite random.
- Tweaking of lightning sequences and improved lighting.
- Addition of dynamic lighting around the bathroom and spawn areas.
- Tedious process of mapping tile by tile has started.
- General fixes and improvements to the spa area of the level.

Alpha 4 -> Final

- Finished tiling process.
- Added a smoother upper border to get rid of blocky feeling.
- Changed flooring around the pool to better accommodate the run-down environment.
- Addition of better lighting around the Side Hall area of the map.
- Texture fixes above the Side spa area, primarily the leaves above the glass.
- Improve soundscapes.
- Improved cubemapping of areas.
- Addition of player clippings to remove access to unintended areas.
- General texture and brush tweaks to improve movement.
- Other minor updates and fixes...

### **Please post your thoughts and ideas! Remember, looking at the screenshots does no justice, please don't be afraid to try it out, even if it's just with bots! If you for some reason would like to make a video preview of the map, that would be lovely. :)**

created by: treebolt


Rules
-------------------------------------
 - pistols only
 - no shooting other players (just the legs of the platform)



Instalation instructions:
-------------------------------------
 - put the map in your maps folder (C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\<username>\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps)


Description
--------------------------------------
     This was a map I made when CS:S was first released. The physics engine inspired me to make a different kind of map involving killing players with objects istead of directly using firearms. If played with the right people, this map can be very fun and is different from the normal type of gameplay.

     You can, of course, use the gun to shoot the other team and kill them, but if you want to have fun and play the map as it was meant to be played, players will instead try to eliminate the other team by shooting the legs of the platforms and making them fall.

de_pinpoint is a bomb plant/defuse map, but it's very uncommon to plant the bomb. There are no hidden paths, no big covers so bomb plants would occure only when there are very few players. The map is very balanced, because terrain is symmetrical. Teams spawn behind a big wedge, Terrorists have 3 "speed-up helpers", that means few bunny hop platforms and 1 short surf ramp, where Terrorists can speed up up to 500 velocity, and get to the middle tower in just seconds.
Counter Terrorists have only 2 barrels to bunnyhop near spawn, because CT's mission is to defend, not assault. Around the whole map there is water, with small depth, when player is standing in water only his head is visible, and when he crouches his whole body is underwater. My map is good for all players - 1 surf ramp, good for bunnyhopping flat terrain, covers, towers, hides. Bunnyhoppers have big advantage, because it's very important to attack the enemy fast, and bunnyhoppers easily avoid bullets in the open terrain. Much ammo is important, because on flat, open terrain you meet all enemies at time, unless some are hiding! Also accuracy is important, because fights can be on very long range, and enemy head is only a few pixels. M4 and AK47 are good weapons for this map, but don't spray, because you don't have much ammo. P90 from SMGs is recommended, because of it's big clip, but you have to be good hopper because of it's inaccuracy at distance. If you are very good hopper and shotgun user you can use them too. M249 is one of the best weapons for this map - accuracy, big clip and high damage. It's only disadvantage is price... Sniper rifles are also recommended, and scout can be good assault rifle for pros. Unfortunately, there is a bug and scout bullet sometimes misses at long distance.
